Class WeatherData

  • java.lang.Object
    • ca.uwo.csd.cs2212.team9.WeatherData

  • public class WeatherData
extends java.lang.Object
    The class retrieves the weather condition for the current day as a JSON string. The JSON string is parsed and stored into a container class. Each individual JSON component have data member associated within the nested class container.
    Author:
    Amha Tsegaye 2212 2015 Team9

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors 
      Constructor and Description
      WeatherData()
      The default constructor for WeatherData class access the API from openweather.org put the JSON file as a string in DataJson data member.
      WeatherData(java.lang.String city)
      An overridden constructor with a string argument that accepts a specific city to get the API from openweather.org and stores the JSON file as a string in DataJson data member.
      WeatherData(java.lang.String city, java.lang.String country)
      An overridden constructor with a string argument that accepts a specific city and country to get the API from openweather.org and stores the JSON file as a string in DataJson data member.

    • Constructor Detail

      • WeatherData

        public WeatherData()
        The default constructor for WeatherData class access the API from openweather.org put the JSON file as a string in DataJson data member. If the URL can not be reached it result in IOException. If successfully retrieves the JSON value it calls the helper class fillDataWeatherData method to update the data members in the DataWeatherData container.

      • WeatherData

        public WeatherData(java.lang.String city)
        An overridden constructor with a string argument that accepts a specific city to get the API from openweather.org and stores the JSON file as a string in DataJson data member. If the URL can not be reached it result in IOException. If successfully retrieves the JSON value it calls the helper class fillDataWeatherData method to update the data members in the DataWeatherData container.
        Parameters:
        city - city name as a string

      • WeatherData

        public WeatherData(java.lang.String city,
                   java.lang.String country)
        An overridden constructor with a string argument that accepts a specific city and country to get the API from openweather.org and stores the JSON file as a string in DataJson data member. If the URL can not be reached it result in IOException. If successfully retrieves the JSON value it calls the helper class fillDataWeatherData method to update the data members in the DataWeatherData container.
        Parameters:
        city - city name as a string
        country - country name as a string

    • Method Detail

      • fillDataWeatherData

        public void fillDataWeatherData()
        A private helper method to load the JSON data from openWeather.org into the the nested class container. Each data is parsed from the JSON string file and stored in specific data member within the class container.

        public java.lang.String checkValidity()
